ave Agency LLC, and Content X, Inc. join in the foregoing motions. [230, 231, 232]. The court finds these matters appropriate for decision without oral argument. See Fed. R. Civ. P. 78(b); C.D. Cal. L.R. 7-15. Accordingly, the hearing set for April 9, 2026, at 10:00 a.m. in Courtroom 10D is VACATED and the court takes the matter UNDER SUBMISSION. THERE IS NO PDF DOCUMENT ASSOCIATED WITH THIS ENTRY. (rrp) TEXT ONLY ENTRY (Entered: 04/06/2026)</summary><link href="https://ecf.cacd.uscourts.gov/cgi-bin/show_case_doc?247,935040,,," length="0" rel="enclosure" /><updated>2026-04-06T00:00:00-07:00</updated></entry><entry><title>Entry #246 in N.Z. v. Fenix International Limited, 8:24-cv-01655</title><link href="https://www.courtlistener.com/docket/68990373/nz-v-fenix-international-limited/?order_by=desc#entry-246" rel="alternate" /><published>2026-04-03T00:00:00-07:00</published><id>https://www.courtlistener.com/docket/68990373/nz-v-fenix-international-limited/?order_by=desc#entry-246</id><summary type="html">Notice of Supplemental Authority filed by Plaintiffs A. L., B. L., R. M., S. M., N. Z.. (Attachments: # 1 Declaration of Richard Garcia-Almendros, # 2 Exhibit A to Garcia-Almendros Declaration)(Carey, Robert) (Entered: 04/03/2026)</summary><link href="https://ecf.cacd.uscourts.gov/doc1/031047413115?caseid=935040" length="0" rel="enclosure" /><updated>2026-04-03T00:00:00-07:00</updated></entry></feed>